	   <tr><td colspan=2>Let me preface this by saying that I am new to Everquest so I may be looking for levels of complexity that aren't ther.&nbsp;&nbsp;My ranger is my one and only char, and the only one that I've played since joining the game.  So, please correct me if I'm wrong.<br><br>It was my understanding that the weapon you put in the primary slot was the one with the highest damage ratio.  This may not be the fastest weapon, and it may not be the hardest hitting weapon.  To give you an example of what I'm talking about.<br><br>1) Faydark Champions Longsword DMG 6 DLY 27  Damage ratio 0.22<br>2) Scimitar                    DMG 5 DLY 25 Damage ratio 0.2<br>3) Silvered Battle Axe         DMG 8 DLY 32 Damage ratio 0.25<br>4) Fading Shadows Longsword    DMG 7 Dly 27 Damage ratio 0.26<br><br>In this example I would have the Fading Shadow Longsword in the primary slot since it does more damage per minute that the 2 swords and the axe.  In this case the Scimitar which is the fastest weapon is actually the worst as it has the lowest damage ratio.  The axe, which is the slowest weapon by far is actually the second best.   This is of course ignoring other factors such as magic abilities.  But if you go to <a href="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ewj/fletchguide/index.htm" target=_new>http://members.bellatlantic.net/~ewj/fletchguide/index.htm</a> there is a discussion on this matter with relation to crafted bows.<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Oct 23 21:57:44 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br>55 season Half Elf Ranger <br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711736" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=711736</a><br>8 song Var Shir Bard <br>level 11 gnome wizard<br>32nd Season Druid<br>Kayne Bayle Server</td></tr>
