	   <tr><td colspan=2>Got a quick tidbit for yall.&nbsp;&nbsp;I am taking a break froma awsome round of exp hunting and thought I should share.  We all know that KC is the defacto place for most lvl 50ish people(or atleast it is on Bristlebane).  I have found that the less people you grp with in here the better the exp is over all.  I read a post a few months back about the EXp grind in DL durring the mid 40's and that the best exp for us rangers there instead of chainpulling is to grp with one shammy, aint this the truth.  I am 51 atm(been so for 4 lvls hehe) and I was just grp with a 51 shammy in KC.  We were pulling from the entrance and eventaly moved to the moat for saftey and to avoid the trains.  She was just keeping me healed and kept hos and regen up and I did te rest, she slowed and sent in her pet.  We made a great team and were raking in the PP drops and most importatnly the exp.  I got 1 yellow in a bout 2 hours which is crazy for me at this lvl.  The only thing that I should let yall now is that we both had C3 and it was slower when we didnt have it(but not that much).  Thought yall should know if you didnt, great exp if you can find one to grp with.  Gotta be a shammy though cause of the slow/heal combo.  You could get a chanter and a cleric to mix it up some and 3 people isnt that bad for exp either.  Well gotta run.  RANGERS LEAD THE WAY  <br>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=414662" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=414662</a><br>-Gavindar Greywulf-<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;  -Pathfinder-<br></td></tr>
